    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> Cajun-style basa</strong> and cook for 3-4 min on each side (your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily)</p><p>Tip: Do not be tempted to turn the fish early, leave it to form a crispy crust!</p>",
